<h1>Logging</h1>

<div class="stat-grid">
  <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-number">16</div><div class="stat-label">Info</div></div>
  <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-number">7</div><div class="stat-label">Warnings</div></div>
  <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-number">5</div><div class="stat-label">Errors</div></div>
  <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-number">2</div><div class="stat-label">Debug</div></div>
</div>

<p>Logging is treated as runtime signal, not ad-hoc debug text. The HR API, Hub API, and Hub consumer all emit structured Laravel logs to <code>stderr</code>, which keeps local Docker output and container-native log collection aligned.</p>

<div class="callout">
  <strong>Message contract:</strong>
  <div class="log-signature">[ClassName][method] Message</div>
  <div class="log-meta">Dynamic values stay in structured context, request correlation is shared with <code>Log::shareContext(...)</code>, and caught throwables use the PSR-3 <code>exception</code> key.</div>
</div>

